{
  "stem": "7506.6",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was starting from-- for my age-- way behind the other boys.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I suppose I'm a quick learner in some respects.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Although the boys, not all Jewish boys at that school, but all English boys at that school, started making fun of me very much because of my inability to speak English.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when I did speak English, it was always with a terrible accent.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It-- it caused me a feeling of less than good, less than the same.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in many respects, that less than the same, or less than equal to, has stuck with me throughout my life.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I've never been able to shake that from me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And yet I know that, in many respects, I'm more than.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I have this terrible, terrible sense of less than.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I then-- when I came out and went to school, I was very much anti-authority.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I couldn't stand being told what to do or where to go or nothing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Nobody could tell me nothing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I knew what they had not the faintest idea of what I knew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I, at that time, even had differences of opinion-- I don't want to call it arguments-- with my uncle, who kitted me out with all new clothes and threw away what I'd got from the camp-- a school uniform, as is the custom in England, to have uniform at school.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But I could not be told by no master in class, by no uncle, or anyone which way was up.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know whether my mother knew whether I was alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What I did know that after I didn't want to remain at school, I wanted to go back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
